name: Café de Flore
description: Iconic Saint‑Germain café with wrap‑around terrace perfect for people‑watching after a riverside walk. Staff are used to well‑behaved dogs on leash; outdoor tables are close together so bring a short lead.

name: Bois de Boulogne – Allée des Chiens
description: The Bois de Boulogne is Paris’s western green lung, and the Allée des Chiens is its most famous off‑leash area. Dogs can run free along shaded forest paths and even swim in small lakes nearby.
